SIMPLE: reprint
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reprint
<hw>Re*print"</hw> <pr>(r?-pr?nt")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To print again; to print a second or a new edition of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To renew the impression of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The whole business of our redemption is . . . to
<qex>reprint</qex> God's image upon the soul.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reprint</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Reprint
<hw>Re"print`</hw> <pr>(r?"pr?nt`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A second or
a new impression or edition of any printed work; specifically, the
publication in one country of a work previously published in
another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reprinter</ent>⟦br⟧
